From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: RK3588 AMDGPU Bringup <noreply@example.com>
Date: Fri, 13 Mar 2026 22:47:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] drm/amdgpu/psp: arm64 skip psp hw_init for RLC backdoor
 bring-up

For arm64 bring-up, allow `fw_load_type=3` to keep PSP `sw_init` artifacts
(notably TOC metadata) while skipping full PSP runtime firmware load in
`psp_hw_init()`, which currently stalls on this platform.
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_psp.c | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_psp.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_psp.c
index 74d9e7442f7d..8e4c71cfcb08 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_psp.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_psp.c
@@ -2635,6 +2635,15 @@ static int psp_hw_init(void *handle)
 	int ret;
 	struct amdgpu_device *adev = (struct amdgpu_device *)handle;
 
+#if defined(CONFIG_ARM64)
+	if (adev->firmware.load_type == AMDGPU_FW_LOAD_RLC_BACKDOOR_AUTO) {
+		dev_info(adev->dev,
+			 "arm64 bring-up: skipping psp hw_init for fw_load_type=%d (TOC from sw_init only)\n",
+			 adev->firmware.load_type);
+		return 0;
+	}
+#endif
+
 	mutex_lock(&adev->firmware.mutex);
 	/*
 	 * This sequence is just used on hw_init only once, no need on
-- 
